BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_312845942@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260303T024147Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260304T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260304T143000
SUMMARY:Python + Agents: Orchestrating advanced multi-agent workflows
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nIn Session 5 of our **Python + Agen
 ts** series\, we’ll go beyond workflow fundamentals and explore how to o
 rchestrate **advanced\, multi‑agent workflows** using the Microsoft Agen
 t Framework.\n\nThis session focuses on patterns that coordinate multiple 
 steps or multiple agents at once\, enabling more powerful and flexible **A
 I‑driven systems**. We’ll begin by comparing **sequential vs. concurre
 nt execution**\, then dive into techniques for running workflow steps in p
 arallel.\n\nYou’ll learn how fan‑out and fan‑in edges enable multipl
 e branches to run at the same time\, how to aggregate their results\, and 
 how concurrency allows workflows to scale across tasks efficiently.\n\nFro
 m there\, we’ll introduce two multi‑agent orchestration approaches tha
 t are built into the framework. We’ll start with **handoff**\, where con
 trol moves entirely from one agent to another based on workflow logic\, wh
 ich is useful for routing tasks to the right agent as the workflow progres
 ses.\n\nWe’ll then look at **Magentic**\, a planning‑oriented supervis
 or that generates a high‑level plan for completing a task and delegates 
 portions of that plan to other agents.\n\nFinally\, we'll wrap up with a d
 emo of an E2E application that showcases a concurrent multi-agent workflow
  in action.\n\n**Prerequisites:** To follow along with the live examples\,
  sign up for a free GitHub account. If you are brand new to generative AI 
 with Python\, start with [our 9-part Python + AI series](https://aka.ms/py
 thonai/rewatch)\, which covers LLMs\, embedding models\, RAG\, tool callin
 g\, MCP\, and more.\n\nPre-requisites:\nTo follow along with the live exam
 ples\, sign up for a free GitHub account. If you are brand new to generati
 ve AI with Python\, start with our [our 9-part Python + AI series](https:/
 /aka.ms/pythonai/rewatch)\, which covers LLMs\, embedding models\, RAG\, t
 ool calling\, MCP\, and more.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3128
 45942/
