SUMMARY:Azure Decoded: When Agents Work Together: Multi-Agent Orchestratio
 n on Azure
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nOne agent is powerful. Multiple age
 nts working together? That's transformational.\n\nIn this session\, we exp
 lore multi-agent orchestration patterns: how to design agent teams\, deleg
 ate tasks\, and coordinate complex workflows. Using Microsoft Agent Framew
 ork and Microsoft Foundry\, you'll see how to build agent systems that div
 ide and conquer problems too complex for a single agent.\n\n**What you'll 
 learn:**\n• When single agents aren't enough (and when they are)\n• Mu
 lti-agent architecture patterns: delegation\, collaboration\, debate\n• 
 Building agent teams with Microsoft Agent Framework\n• Coordinating comp
 lex workflows across agents\n• Real-world use cases: research assistants
 \, code review teams\, customer service escalation\n\n**Who should attend:
 ** Developers who've built their first agent and want to scale up to multi
 -agent solutions.\n\n-----------------------------------------------------
 --\nExplore the Learn paths:\n- [Build a foundation to build AI agents and
  extend Microsoft 365 Copilot](https://learn.microsoft.com/training/paths/
 build-foundation-extend-microsoft-365-copilot/?wt.mc_id=meetup_26843_webpa
 ge_reactor)\n- [Develop AI agents on Azure](https://learn.microsoft.com/tr
 aining/paths/develop-ai-agents-on-azure/?wt.mc_id=meetup_26843_webpage_rea
 ctor)\n\n📌 This session is a part of a series! Learn more [**here**](ht
 tps://developer.microsoft.com/reactor/series/S-1644/?wt.mc_id=meetup_S-164
 4_webpage_reactor)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3134
 22942/
